com.github.mk23.jmxproxy.core

Class MBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mk23.jmxproxy.core.MBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonSerializable

    public class MBean
extends Object
implements com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonSerializable

    JMX MBean tracker and serializer.

    Maintains a map of JMX Attribute names and a History of their values. Implements JsonSerializable interface to convert the stored map into JSON.
    Since:
    2015-05-11
    Version:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    mk23
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • addAttribute

        public final void addAttribute(String attributeName,
                               Object attributeObject,
                               int historySize)

        Inserts a new Attribute name to History association.

        Optionally creates a new History object and inserts into the map store associating it to the specified attribute name. Appends the specified Attribute value to the History.
        Parameters:
        attributeName - name of the Attribute used as the map key.
        attributeObject - value of the Attribute added to history.
        historySize - number of items to preserve in the associated History.

      • setLimit

        public final MBean setLimit(Integer bound)

        Sets the thread local history request limit.

        Set the thread local limit for all History when serializing to JSON. Because this method returns its object, requesting serialization can be done with a single statement.

        For example

        return Response.ok(mbean.setLimit(5)).build();
        Parameters:
        bound - the number of items to retreive from History for this thread.
        Returns:
        this mbean object for chaining calls.
        See Also:
        javax.ws.rs.core.Response

      • hasAttribute

        public final boolean hasAttribute(String attribute)

        Tester for attribute name.

        Checks for requested Attribute name in the map store.
        Parameters:
        attribute - name of the Attribute to look up in the map store.
        Returns:
        true if the Attribute exists in the map store, false otherwise.

      • getAttributes

        public final Set<String> getAttributes()

        Getter for attribute names.

        Extracts and returns the unique Set of all currently stored Attribute names.
        Returns:
        Set of Attribute name Strings.

      • getAttribute

        public final Attribute getAttribute(String attribute)

        Getter for most recent attribute.

        Fetches the most recent Attribute value for the specified name from the associated History in the map store.
        Parameters:
        attribute - name of the Attribute to look up in the map store.
        Returns:
        latest Attribute object from History if found, null otherwise.

      • getAttributes

        public final List<Attribute> getAttributes(String attribute,
                                           int bound)

        Getter for a subset of historical attribute values.

        Fetches an array, limited by the requested bound, of most recent Attribute values for the specified name from the associated History in the map store.
        Parameters:
        attribute - name of the Attribute to look up in the map store.
        bound - size of the resulting array or full history if this exceeds capacity or less than 1.
        Returns:
        List of the latest Attribute objects from History if found, empty otherwise.
